TRIANGULAR PIN GRID, TILING CODES, AND BLUE LINE SKELETON
kind-pasteur-2026-03-14-S76
======================================================================

======================================================================
PART 1: THE TRIANGULAR PIN GRID
======================================================================

  n=4: m=3 tiles on delta_{2}
  Pin grid:
    r=1: ['(3,1)', '(4,2)']
    r=2: ['(4,1)']

  GS symmetry (r,c) -> (r, 4-r-c):
    Fixed points: [(2, 1)]
    Paired positions: 1
    GS degrees of freedom: 2
    #GS tilings = 2^(2) = 4

  n=5: m=6 tiles on delta_{3}
  Pin grid:
    r=1: ['(3,1)', '(4,2)', '(5,3)']
    r=2: ['(4,1)', '(5,2)']
    r=3: ['(5,1)']

  GS symmetry (r,c) -> (r, 5-r-c):
    Fixed points: [(1, 2), (3, 1)]
    Paired positions: 2
    GS degrees of freedom: 4
    #GS tilings = 2^(4) = 16

  n=6: m=10 tiles on delta_{4}
  Pin grid:
    r=1: ['(3,1)', '(4,2)', '(5,3)', '(6,4)']
    r=2: ['(4,1)', '(5,2)', '(6,3)']
    r=3: ['(5,1)', '(6,2)']
    r=4: ['(6,1)']

  GS symmetry (r,c) -> (r, 6-r-c):
    Fixed points: [(2, 2), (4, 1)]
    Paired positions: 4
    GS degrees of freedom: 6
    #GS tilings = 2^(6) = 64

  n=7: m=15 tiles on delta_{5}
  Pin grid:
    r=1: ['(3,1)', '(4,2)', '(5,3)', '(6,4)', '(7,5)']
    r=2: ['(4,1)', '(5,2)', '(6,3)', '(7,4)']
    r=3: ['(5,1)', '(6,2)', '(7,3)']
    r=4: ['(6,1)', '(7,2)']
    r=5: ['(7,1)']

  GS symmetry (r,c) -> (r, 7-r-c):
    Fixed points: [(1, 3), (3, 2), (5, 1)]
    Paired positions: 6
    GS degrees of freedom: 9
    #GS tilings = 2^(9) = 512

