PART 2: GS TILINGS AS A LINEAR CODE
  GS constraint: tile(r,c) = tile(r, n-2-r-c)
  This is a linear constraint over F_2
======================================================================

  n=5: m=6, GS dim = 4, rate = 0.6667
    #GS codewords = 16

  GS tiling H distribution:
    H=1: 1 GS tilings
    H=3: 1 GS tilings
    H=9: 4 GS tilings
    H=11: 3 GS tilings
    H=13: 3 GS tilings
    H=15: 4 GS tilings

  Weight distribution of GS tilings:
    weight 0: 1
    weight 1: 2
    weight 2: 3
    weight 3: 4
    weight 4: 3
    weight 5: 2
    weight 6: 1

  Self-flip analysis:
    Blueself (GS + self-flip same H): 2 tilings
    Expected: 0 (THM-023: blueself requires even n)

